The paper deals with multi-agent learning in network zero-sum games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also establishes a connection between multi-agent systems and Hamiltonian dynamics, which is a topic that falls under control systems (cs.SY) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses online learning dynamics, which is a topic that falls under neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.GT and cs.LG, followed by cs.SY, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
